Task: Develop Stock Inventory Management System(SIMS)
As a full stack developer, you are given 7 hours to develop that web based
application by:
1.Using attributes provided below , design an entity relationship diagram
(ERD)that represents relation ship between their entities.
> identify appropriate primary keys and foreign keys based on the
relationship between their entities.
> Entities and attributes are:
1. Spare_Part (Name, Category,Quantity, UnitPrice, TotalPrice)
2.Stock_In ( StockInQuantity, StockInDate)
3.Stock_Out (StockOutQuantity, StockOutUnitPrice,
StockOutTotalPrice,StockOutDate)
>ERD should be drawn before using the computer.
>ERD should be drawn on plain paper using pencils
>ERD should be indicates cardinalities , relationships with correct symbols

2. creating database called SIMS with Spare_Part, Stock_In, Stock_Out
tables as designed in ERD above.

3. Preparing React.js Front_end application environment by installing
required modules and dependencies

4. Prepare Javascript runtime environment for Node.js

5. creating react.js components with ui features that will enable user to
input his data in the tables above and display required reports.
>Menu bar/pages of web application should include spare_part , stock_in and
stock_out, reports and logout options

6. Developing backend and frontend  of parking sales management system.
> Name backend folder as backend-project and frontend folder as
frontend-project.
>Use tailwind CSS to implement UI design.
>Your backend application should communicate to MYSQL database to perform
CRUD operations  of using Node.js runtime environment and express.js
framework.

Note: 1. Insert operation should be used on all four (4) forms (Spare_part,
stock_in and stock_out)
         2. Delete , Update , Retirieve operations should only be used on
Stock_out form

7. Creating a session based login user account having username and
password.|
       > Password must be strong and encrypted

8. Integrating your react.js application using Axios to enable interaction
of your react.js application  with node.js application .

9. Generating daily StockOut report

10.Generating daily Stock status composed by spare part name , stored
Quantity , StockOut and remaining Quantity.

